away laughing
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:off to a good start; in the lead, well ahead, winning (in literal and transferred senses) (cf similar expressions: laugh all the way to the bank, (P8:1965) couldn't laugh for the lolly).]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Poss. a var. of P8: be laughing--> WW1 WW2 `be safe', etc and later `be winning'] x-ref. only at AWAY ca1950 (Les Cleveland)
